{
  "_rules": {
    "zeroing": "event_id is set to the empty string and sig to null before hashing (RFC-0002 s4)",
    "genesis": "prev_hash of a run's first event is 64 zero hex chars",
    "verify_cases": "each case feeds its events, in order, to the single-run chain verifier; expected names the FIRST failure: code CHAIN_BROKEN with the seq and run_id of the event where verification broke. Run uniformity is a chain property: input spanning two run_ids is a broken chain at the first event whose run_id diverges from the first event's (RFC-0002 D4), not a caller-precondition violation",
    "seal_cases": "each case seals the recorded event: zeroing is unconditional, so a non-empty recorded event_id and a present sig are both ignored for hashing; expected_event_id is the re-derived identity",
    "runs": "additional self-contained mini-runs verified exactly like the top-level events: per-event event_id re-derivation, genesis-onward linkage, expected_head. An event whose sig is non-null seals identically to the same event with sig null (sig is zeroed for hashing, RFC-0002 s5); the harness asserts that equality for every signed event",
    "event_id": "sha256 of the canonical form of the zeroed envelope"
  },
